The paper explores the use of visual questions for personality tests, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for image processing. The estimation of personality traits through image preferences also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) technologies. Additionally, the paper discusses the identification of concepts and selection of image options, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
